n followed by masking might also work, the explicit conditional check is clearer for modulo arithmetic.\n*   Since there is no combinational logic block driving the output separately (the output `q` is the register itself), the `always @(*)` constraint is not strictly necessary, but it's good practice to ensure any implied combinational logic (like the next state calculation) is robust, which is handled by the sequential update in this case.",
